article.headline: San Jose State defeats UC Irvine 72-64
article.description: — Trey Anderson had 19 points in San Jose State's 72-64 win against UC Irvine on Tuesday night in the season opener for both teams.
article.linkText: San Jose State defeats UC Irvine 72-64
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. -- — Trey Anderson had 19 points in San Jose State's 72-64 win against UC Irvine on Tuesday night in the season opener for both teams. Anderson was 7-of-9 shooting, including 2 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 3 for 4 from the line for the Spartans. Tibet Gorener scored 17 points and added five rebounds. Myron Amey Jr. had 12 points and shot 3 of 8 from the field and 6 for 6 from the line. Bent Leuchten finished with 14 points and six rebounds for the Anteaters. Devin Tillis added 12 points for UC Irvine. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
